{"pageProps":{"tutorial":{"title":"CSS Text Styling","slug":"css-text-styling","subject":"CSS","category":"Web Development","level":"Beginner","estimated_read_time":"15 mins","prerequisites":["CSS Colors"],"learning_objectives":["Learn text-color","Learn text-align","Learn text-decoration","Learn text-transform","Learn letter-spacing and line-height","Learn text-shadow"],"theory":"CSS provides powerful tools to style text content.\n\n*   `color`: Sets text color.\n*   `text-align`: Horizontal alignment (left, right, center, justify).\n*   `text-decoration`: Used for underlines, overlines, and removing link underlines.\n*   `text-transform`: Controls capitalization (uppercase, lowercase, capitalize).\n*   `line-height`: Sets the distance between lines of text.\n*   `letter-spacing`: Increases/decreases space between characters.","syntax":"p {\n  color: blue;\n  text-align: justify;\n  text-decoration: none;\n  text-transform: uppercase;\n  line-height: 1.6;\n}","examples":[{"code":"a {\n  text-decoration: none;\n}","output":"Removes the underline from hyperlinks.","explanation":"Standard practice for navigation menus."}],"common_mistakes":[{"mistake":"Using 'text-align' to center block elements","correction":"`text-align: center` only centers text and inline elements. To center a div, use margin: auto.","example":""}],"interview_questions":[{"question":"How do you remove the underline from links?","answer":"`text-decoration: none;`","difficulty":"Easy"},{"question":"What is the difference between `visibility: hidden` and `display: none`?","answer":"Visibility: hidden hides text but keeps space. Display: none removes it from the flow entirely.","difficulty":"Medium"}],"practice_problems":[{"problem":"Make all <p> text CAPITALIZED.","hint":"Use text-transform.","solution":"p { text-transform: uppercase; }","difficulty":"Easy"}],"real_world_use_cases":[{"scenario":"Readable Articles","description":"Blogs use `line-height: 1.6` and `text-align: left` for optimal readabil